#: src/format/theme/index.md:1
msgid "Theme"
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:3
msgid ""
"The default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template "
"to render your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the "
"mdBook binary."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:7
msgid ""
"The theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file "
"from the theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` "
"folder in your project root. Create a new file with the name of the file you "
"want to override and now that file will be used instead of the default file."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:12
msgid "Here are the files you can override:"
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:14
msgid "**_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:15
msgid "**_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:16
msgid "**_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:17
msgid "**_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:18
msgid "**_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:19
msgid "**_css/general.css_** is the base styles."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:20
msgid "**_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:21
msgid "**_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:22
msgid ""
"**_book.js_** is mostly used to add client side functionality, like hiding / "
"un-hiding the sidebar, changing the theme, ..."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:24
msgid ""
"**_highlight.js_** is the JavaScript that is used to highlight code "
"snippets, you should not need to modify this."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:26
msgid "**_highlight.css_** is the theme used for the code highlighting."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:27
msgid ""
"**_favicon.svg_** and **_favicon.png_** the favicon that will be used. The "
"SVG version is used by [newer browsers](https://caniuse.com/#feat=link-icon-"
"svg)."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:29
msgid ""
"**fonts/fonts.css** contains the definition of which fonts to load. Custom "
"fonts can be included in the `fonts` directory."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:32
msgid ""
"Generally, when you want to tweak the theme, you don't need to override all "
"the files. If you only need changes in the stylesheet, there is no point in "
"overriding all the other files. Because custom files take precedence over "
"built-in ones, they will not get updated with new fixes / features."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:37
msgid ""
"**Note:** When you override a file, it is possible that you break some "
"functionality. Therefore I recommend to use the file from the default theme "
"as template and only add / modify what you need. You can copy the default "
"theme into your source directory automatically by using `mdbook init --"
"theme` and just remove the files you don't want to override."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:43
msgid ""
"`mdbook init --theme` will not create every file listed above. Some files, "
"such as `head.hbs`, do not have built-in equivalents. Just create the file "
"if you need it."
msgstr ""

#: src/format/theme/index.md:47
msgid ""
"If you completely replace all built-in themes, be sure to also set [`output."
"html.preferred-dark-theme`](../configuration/renderers.md#html-renderer-"
"options) in the config, which defaults to the built-in `navy` theme."
msgstr ""
